Package com.example.plannet.Event

Class Event

java.lang.Object
com.example.plannet.Event.Event
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Event extends Object implements Serializable
Stores event attributes such as name, image, price, maximum entrants, waitlist limit, dates, description, geolocation status, and facility information.

    • Event

      public Event(String eventName, String price, int maxEntrants, int limitWaitlist, Date eventDate, Date registrationDateDeadline, Date registrationStartDate, String description, boolean geolocation, String facility)
      Constructor. Creates an event and fills all the attributes. NOTE for part 4 polishing: add default values for optional attributes
      Parameters:
      eventName - The name of the event.
      price - The price for the event as a String (optional).
      maxEntrants - The maximum number of entrants allowed (optional).
      limitWaitlist - The limit for waitlist entries (optional).
      eventDate - The date the event will happen.
      registrationDateDeadline - The registration deadline.
      registrationStartDate - The start date for registration.
      description - A description of the event (String).
      geolocation - True if geolocation is required, false if not.
      facility - The facility where the event is.

    • generateEventID

      public String generateEventID()
      Called whenever an event is created. Generates a unique event ID by combining the event name and the current time.
      Returns:
      The generated unique event ID as a String.
